---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead
			title="Privacy Policy | TikaTiles"
			description="Privacy policy for the TikaTiles website and game prototype."
		/>
	</head>
	<body>
		<Header />
		<main class="legal-page prose">
			<p class="legal-kicker">Last updated: June 26, 2026</p>
			<h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
			<p>
				This Privacy Policy explains how tikatiles.com handles information when you visit the
				website or try the browser-based game prototype.
			</p>

			<h2>Information You Provide</h2>
			<p>
				If you email TikaTiles, the information you send, including your email address and
				message content, may be used to reply to you and keep a record of the conversation.
			</p>

			<h2>Information Stored on Your Device</h2>
			<p>
				The website uses browser local storage to remember your light or dark theme preference
				and to store limited local game prototype interaction data. This information stays in
				your browser unless you choose to send it separately.
			</p>

			<h2>Analytics and Cookies</h2>
			<p>
				The website may use Google Analytics 4 to understand aggregate website traffic and
				marketing performance, such as pages visited, approximate location, device type,
				referring source, and clicks on key links. Google Analytics may use cookies or similar
				technologies to provide these measurements. Hosting providers may also process standard
				technical data, such as IP address, browser type, pages requested, and timestamps, to
				deliver and secure the website.
			</p>

			<h2>Children</h2>
			<p>
				TikaTiles is being designed for kids and families, but this website is intended for
				parents, caregivers, educators, and interested adults. The website does not knowingly
				request personal information from children. If you believe a child has sent personal
				information, contact TikaTiles so it can be deleted.
			</p>

			<h2>How Information Is Used</h2>
			<p>
				Information may be used to respond to messages, improve the website and prototype,
				debug technical issues, protect the site, and understand interest in the product.
			</p>

			<h2>Sharing</h2>
			<p>
				TikaTiles does not sell personal information. Information may be shared with service
				providers who help operate the website or email, or when required by law.
			</p>

			<h2>Data Choices</h2>
			<p>
				You can clear local storage in your browser settings. You can also contact
				<a href="mailto:info@tikatiles.com">info@tikatiles.com</a> to request deletion of
				information you previously emailed.
			</p>

			<h2>Future Updates</h2>
			<p>
				If TikaTiles adds accounts, app features, purchases, waitlists, advertising features,
				or other data collection, this policy should be updated before those features launch.
			</p>
		</main>
		<Footer />
	</body>
</html>

<style>
	.legal-page {
		padding-top: clamp(2rem, 6vw, 5rem);
	}

	.legal-kicker {
		margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
		color: var(--accent);
		font-size: 0.82rem;
		font-weight: 800;
		letter-spacing: 0.08em;
		text-indent: 0;
		text-transform: uppercase;
	}

	.legal-page h1 {
		font-size: clamp(2.75rem, 8vw, 5.5rem);
		line-height: 0.95;
	}

	.legal-page h2 {
		margin-top: 2rem;
		font-size: clamp(1.35rem, 3vw, 2rem);
	}

	.legal-page p {
		color: rgb(var(--gray-dark));
		text-indent: 0;
	}
</style>
